# English Naming Conventions

All code elements must be written in English, including:
- Variables and constants
- Function and method names
- Class names
- Database table and column names
- Comments and documentation
- File names

## Examples

```php
// ❌ BAD - Portuguese names
$nomeUsuario = 'João';
$dataAtual = now();
function buscarColmeias() {}
class GerenciadorAbelhas {}

// ✅ GOOD - English names
$userName = 'João';
$currentDate = now();
function fetchHives() {}
class BeeManager {}
```

```php
// ❌ BAD - Mixed Portuguese/English
public function salvarDados($informacoes) {
    $resultado = $this->processar($informacoes);
    return $resultado;
}

// ✅ GOOD - Consistent English
public function saveData($information) {
    $result = $this->process($information);
    return $result;
}
```

## Database Naming

```php
// ❌ BAD
Schema::create('usuarios', function (Blueprint $table) {
    $table->string('nome');
    $table->string('sobrenome');
});

// ✅ GOOD
Schema::create('users', function (Blueprint $table) {
    $table->string('first_name');
    $table->string('last_name');
});
```

